history.content:
Any declared CS or EECS major who has tried to enroll in CS upper division courses and is still having trouble (try one more time please), I'm going to suggest you fill out a service now ticket @ https://berkeley.service-now.com/ess/create_incident

In the request for service, you should say "I am a declared LSCS or EECS major and the department believes it has screened for enrollment so that all declared LSCS or EECS majors should be able to enroll in upper div cs classes (except for 169 where all students have to waitlist).  How can I enroll? Is there something that needs to be fixed at a campus level or can you tell me what I can do? (Or communicate with department staff @ sasson@berkeley.edu if there is something he can do.)"

Similarly, if you are declared EECS or undeclared LS (entering 2nd or 3rd year at Cal) and unable to sign up for 61C or 70, please submit a similar request to https://berkeley.service-now.com/ess/create_incident 

Thanks!
